The Eternal Dungeon is an instanced endless dungeon run for a solo
player or a small group.

Once you enter, your run is private to your party. Each floor is
generated for that run, filled with themed rooms, enemies, objectives,
affixes, and a final leader encounter.

Basic commands:

  eternal enter [floor]
  eternal status
  eternal leave
  eternal rejoin
  eternal leaderboard [v2|legacy]
  eternal choose <1-3>

How it works:

  1. Enter the dungeon.
  2. Complete the floor objective.
  3. A portal opens with one or more route choices.
  4. Use portal <route> or enter portal <route> to advance.
  5. Repeat until the run wipes.

Some objectives happen before the final leader. If the dungeon asks you
to recover a relic or cleanse a shrine, the object will appear in an
earlier chamber and the room description will show the exact command:
recover relic or cleanse shrine. The final portal will not open until
the objective and the leader are both handled.

Routes can include safe, elite, boss, or unstable paths. Harder routes
pay more Eternal Shards, but they also make the next floor more
dangerous.

Every few floors the dungeon may offer a bargain. The run leader can
use eternal choose <1-3> to accept one of the offered boons or curses
before advancing.

Deaths inside the Eternal Dungeon are not normal deaths. If the run
fails, players are returned safely and rewarded based on how far the run
advanced.

Your progress is tracked, including runs, kills, defeats, and highest
floor reached. Personal best floors can also be announced on Events when
you surpass your old record. Eternal v2 has its own leaderboard and
shard progress. Legacy records remain visible with eternal leaderboard
legacy.

Checkpoints unlock every 5 floors. Solo checkpoints belong to the
player who unlocked them. Group checkpoints belong to the exact party
composition that unlocked them, so the same players must reunite to use
those group checkpoints.

Use eternal enter [floor] to start from an unlocked checkpoint. Use
eternal status to view your available solo checkpoints and, when your
party is assembled, any group checkpoints for that composition.

Leaderboard entries show the starting floor when a run began from a
checkpoint. Skipped floors do not grant reward compensation. V2 and
legacy leaderboards are separate because the dungeon rules are different.

See also: help eternal, help boss_tiers

Reward Chests
-------------
Every leader or boss kill leaves a personal reward chest for each member
present in the run. Chests are name-locked, fade after ten minutes, and
do not follow you through the portal - open yours before advancing.

Chest quality is earned, not farmed:

  - The FIRST chest of each reward tier you earn per real day is GILDED:
    full rolls, a guaranteed rare roll, and the only grade that can ever
    hold a permanent relic.
  - The next two chests of that tier the same day are PLAIN (fewer
    rolls, no guarantees).
  - After that, and whenever you fight roughly ten or more floors below
    your personal best, chests dim to SHARD CACHES: a small Eternal
    Shard payout, no premium treasure, and a modest chance at crafting
    material.

Each member's chest is scaled to their own record, so carrying a
lower-floor friend gives them real chests while your own reflect your
personal best. Chest contents include consumables, ember crafting
materials and recipe cards for the professions, timed emberforged gear
that burns away when its ember is spent, and - very rarely, from deep
gilded chests - permanent relics that the dungeon yields at most once
per adventurer in their lifetime.

Crafting supply is rolled separately from premium treasure. Gilded chests
guarantee two materials, plain chests guarantee one, and shard caches may
still yield one. Recipe cards only appear in gilded or plain chests and
match the effective reward tier: Emberdraught at low tiers, Phoenix Tonic
through the middle tiers, and Emberforged Whetstone at the deepest tier.
Each eligible chest without a card advances that tier's pity counter; once
five misses are shown, the next eligible chest guarantees a card. Use
'eternal status' to inspect those counters.

The shard shop ('eternal shop') also carries permanent items at fixed
prices, likewise one per adventurer, ever. It also sells persistent,
tradeable ember materials and recipe cards at fixed prices so shard caches
remain a deterministic path into Eternal crafting. 'eternal status' shows
how many premium chests of each tier you have earned today.
